race.comment: ZOUQUA (12) trialled well and then sat on pace when beaten 2L at Goulburn on debut. Had a poor recovery rate, but she's had three weeks to freshen and jumps from an inside barrier with a 2kg claimer aboard. In a top Sydney yard and is well placed to win. C'MON WICKSY (1) has been within range both starts this preparation and is ready to find his best. Jumps from the inside barrier, and the blinkers are applied for the first time. A live chance. COMMON GOAL (2) lost his rider at Canberra before the spell, jumping at a short quote. Resumed at Newcastle over 1300m and found one too good when beaten 2.5L. That effort stacks right up and Owen replaced the 3kg apprentice. The gate is awkwardly but he also has winning claims. TRUST YOUR CAPE (10) has an inside gate and a key jockey switch to Heywood. We should see more from her third-up. STOCK ROAD (3) just missed over this distance at Bathurst but has an outside barrier and that will test.
